    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker** anchoring the lineup, serving as our primary engines for production. **Gunnar Henderson** leads the squad with an elite 81.87 score, buoyed by a significant +16% park adjustment and a favorable matchup against Bello. While he carries a 34% rain risk, his leadoff spot and platoon advantage against a right-hander make him a must-start. **Kyle Tucker** continues to be a high-floor producer with a 73.74 score, benefiting from a soft matchup against Taillon. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a steady force (66.24), offering a reliable foundation at 1B despite the dynamic platoon variance. We are also banking on **Nasim Nunez** (60.13) and **Andy Pages** (60.68) to provide efficient middle-of-the-order output, with **Nasim Nunez** notably leveraging his switch-hitting ability to navigate the matchup against Hudson.\n\nThe most difficult decision of the day involved **Brady House**, who sat just outside the starting threshold with a score of 52.73. While his 19% SP skill adjustment against Hudson is attractive, the optimizer favored the higher raw production ceiling offered by our current UTIL and MI slots. Additionally, **Marcell Ozuna** was considered but ultimately benched due to a projected struggle against the elite arm of Woodruff (2.90 xERA), which suppresses his scoring potential well below our preferred levels. Investors should monitor the rain risk in the game featuring **Gunnar Henderson** and **Coby Mayo**, as any delay could dampen our stolen base opportunities. Lastly, keep a close eye on **Heliot Ramos**, whose score of 58.46 is bolstered by a +2% aggressive baserunning modifier against a slow-delivering pitcher, potentially providing a sneaky source of SBs if he can reach base early against Alcantara.",
